<ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">organism culturing</ENAMEX> or testing areas, and from testing and sample
preparation areas into culture <ENAMEX TYPE="FAC_DESC">rooms</ENAMEX>.


4.2.2
Laboratory and toxicity test
temperature control equipment must be adequate to maintain
recommended test water temperatures. Recommended <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">materials</ENAMEX> must be
used in the fabrication of the test equipment which comes in
contact with the effluent (see Section 5, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Facilities, Equipment</ENAMEX> and
Supplies; and specific toxicity test method).


4.3
<ENAMEX TYPE="PRODUCT">TEST ORGANISMS</ENAMEX>




4.3.1
The test organisms used in the procedures described in
this manual are the fathead minnow, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Pimephales</ENAMEX> promelas, the
